=== Etymology ===
Latin ''Pangaea'' from Greek [[παγγαία]] (pangaía), from [[πάν]] (pán) "all" + [[γή]] (gē) "[[earth]]"; coined by [[w:Alfred Wegener|Alfred Wegener]] in 1915.

===Hyphenation===
pan·gae·a

===Proper noun===
'''Pangaea'''

#A [[supercontinent]] that included all the [[landmass]]es of the [[earth]] before the [[Triassic Period]] and that broke up into [[Laurasia]] and [[Gondwana]].

